name: train production, passenger, regional | train, passenger, regional | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/6044/documentation

Based on "train production, passenger, regional, CH 2000). The exchanges of the train manufacturing are derived from an assessment of the "Kolibri", a regional train which is currently used for regional transportation in Switzerland .The life span of the train  is assumed to be 40 years resulting in a life time performance of  6’000’000 vkm.  Total weight of the train is about 171t. The dominating material is steel.

Service starts with the material consumption for the production of the regional train.

This inventory calls processes of material production, representing the material composition of a standard Swiss Regional Train (Kolibri). For manufacturing, electricity and light oil burned in industrial furnace are included. For the transportation of materials standard distance are applied. The disposal of the regional train is included as well.
category: C:Manufacturing/30:Manufacture of other transport equipment/302:Manufacture of railway locomotives and rolling stock/3020:Manufacture of railway locomotives and rolling stock

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Extrapolated from "train production, passenger, regional, CH 2000). Manufacturing data represents a train produced in Europe.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: In 2000 the modelled train dominates the regional transport in Switzerland. However, in the near future new trains will be in operation, which are characterised by a substitution of steel with aluminium.;References:;Frischknecht R., Bollens U., Bosshart S., Ciot M., Ciseri L., Doka G., Dones R., Gantner U. and Hischier R. (1996) Ökoinventare von Energiesystemen: Grundlagen für den ökologischen Vergleich von Energiesystemen und den Einbezug von Energiesystemen in Ökobilanzen für die Schweiz. Auflage No. 3. Gruppe Energie - Stoffe - Umwelt (ESU), Eidgenössische Technische Hochschule Zuerich und Sektion Ganzheitliche Systemanalysen, Paul Scherrer Institut, Villigen, Bundesamt für Energie (Hrsg.), Bern
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: This train type is used as an estimate for the entire regional train fleet. This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The data of the material composition and energy consumption is based on oral communication with an expert of one company and literature studies.
